            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-17T10:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-17T10:15:00-05:00" n="894" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d894">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.32/2–1745: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-17T18:15:00+03:00">February 17, 1945—6:15 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 3—6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–40. Reference is made to the Department’s airmail instruction no. 429 of
                    January 26, 1945.<note n="54" xml:id="d894fn54">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Ensign Byron Uskievich was married on September 18, 1944 to Margarita Nikitichna
                    Osipova. On October 28, Mrs. Uskievich filed a petition for the renunciation of
                    Soviet citizenship. On December 6 the Embassy wrote a note to the Foreign Office
                    requesting that the competent Soviet authorities be informed of its interest in
                    Mrs. Uskievich’s case and its hope that action would be taken on it at an early
                    date. To this communication no reply has been received. Ensign Uskievich left
                    Moscow for the United States of [<hi rend="italic">on</hi>] February 14,
                    1945.</p>
                <p>The Embassy will give Mrs. Uskievich all possible assistance in her effort to
                    obtain permission to leave the Soviet Union.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
